== EPs ==

An EP is a shorter collection of songs, usually 4-7, although they can have more. 'Spanish Goat Dancer' by Head Like a Hole was released as an EP<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spanish_Goat_Dancer</ref>, despite having 20 songs, although most of these were not album quality recordings. A record with less than 4 songs is usually released as a single.

